U.S. District Judge Paul Barbadoro dismissed a claim seeking damages for Tyco related to fraud and corporate looting.
However, shareholders can proceed with a class action lawsuit against the company.
Former executives Kozlowski and Swartz face retrial for stealing $600 million from Tyco.
Prosecutors allege they hid bonuses and inflated stock prices.
The trial focuses on their lavish lifestyle and alleged thefts.
Legal experts predict a leaner case this time.
The prosecution aims to prove criminal intent.
Defense lawyers argue the actions were approved by the board.
The trial highlights corporate scandals and criminal enforcement in the business world.
